* Description

  This repository is for CM 10.1 on Samsung X Cover 2 a.k.a Samsung Skomer.
  It's still a work in progress. Use this at your own risk!

* How To Build CM 10.1 for Samsung Skomer

  - Do repo init & sync

  $ repo init -u git://github.com/CyanogenMod/android.git -b cm-10.1

  - Create .repo/local_manifest.xml with the following content:

  <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
  <manifest>
     <project path="device/samsung/skomer" name="flxo/android_device_samsung_skomer" />
     <project path="kernel/samsung/skomer" name="flxo/android_kernel_samsung_skomer" revision="jellybean" />
     <project path="device/samsung/u8500-common" name="flxo/android_device_samsung_u8500-common" />
     <project path="vendor/samsung/u8500-common" name="flxo/android_vendor_samsung_u8500-common" />
     <project path="hardware/u8500" name="TeamCanjica/android_hardware_u8500" />
     <remove-project name="CyanogenMod/android_hardware_libhardware" />
     <project path="hardware/libhardware" name="TeamCanjica/android_hardware_libhardware" />
  </manifest>

  $ repo sync

  - Setup vendor

  $ ./vendor/cm/get-prebuilts

  - Pull all OMX fixes from gerrit:

  $ ./device/samsung/skomer/pull

  - Setup environment

  $ source build/envsetup.sh
  $ lunch cm_skomer-eng


  - Build

  $ export USE_CCACHE=1
  $ make -jX otapackage


